  <h2>How It Works</h2>
  <p>
    LocalPDF uses client-side JavaScript libraries to manipulate PDFs directly in your browser:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>pdf-lib</strong> ‚Äî For merging, splitting, compressing, and protecting PDFs</li>
    <li><strong>PDF.js</strong> ‚Äî Mozilla's open-source PDF renderer for previews and OCR</li>
    <li><strong>Tesseract.js</strong> ‚Äî OCR engine that extracts text from scanned documents</li>
    <li><strong>React 19</strong> ‚Äî Modern UI framework for smooth interactions</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    When you upload a file, it stays in your browser's memory. Processing happens using WebAssembly and
    JavaScript‚Äîno network requests, no server communication. When you download the result, the file is
    generated locally and saved to your device.
